headline: Trump To Change Dollar Stores For Good? Dollar Tree Exec Says 'Prepared To Act'
summary: A proposal by Donald Trump to impose tariffs on products that come to the U.S. from China, Canada and Mexico could have an impact on products and their prices found in American dollar stores. What Happened: For years, dollar stores have offered items across their aisles that cost $1 or less in many cases. That has changed over the years with dollar stores owned by Dollar Tree Inc (NASDAQ:DLTR) raising prices to $1.25 to offset higher inflation. Trump's tariff plans could mean further price hikes
